What is java?
Java is popular programming language which is developed in 1995 by james gosling at sun micorsuytems but iti is currently owned by the oracle.Java follows the write once
run anywhere principle . Meaning that once we write the java code that can be run on any platform.Java is a high level programming language which can be used to build the
software applications.Java is used to build the programmes like mobile apps , web appplications , deaktop software and even large systems like banking software.
It is object-oriented means it organizes code uisng the objects like real world things to make programs easier to design and manage.It is known for being secure 
reliable and widely used.

